# Fixed Sliding Window

643. Maximum Average Subarray I

Idea:
Find the maximum average of a window of size k.

Store:
Window Sum

Window:
Fixed

Return:
Maximum Average

---------------------------------------------------------

1343. Number of Sub-arrays of Size K and Average Greater than or Equal to Threshold

Idea:
Count how many windows satisfy average >= threshold.

Store:
Window Sum

Window:
Fixed

Return:
Count

---------------------------------------------------------

567. Permutation in String

Idea:
Check whether s2 contains any permutation of s1.

Store:
Need Frequency
Window Frequency

Window:
Fixed

Return:
True / False

---------------------------------------------------------

# Variable Sliding Window

3. Longest Substring Without Repeating Characters

Idea:
Longest substring with unique characters.

Store:
Character Set

Valid:
No duplicates

Return:
Maximum Length

---------------------------------------------------------

904. Fruit Into Baskets

Idea:
Longest window containing at most two fruit types.

Store:
Fruit -> Frequency

Valid:
Distinct Fruits <= 2

Return:
Maximum Length

---------------------------------------------------------

209. Minimum Size Subarray Sum

Idea:
Smallest window whose sum >= target.

Store:
Window Sum

Valid:
Sum >= Target

Return:
Minimum Length

---------------------------------------------------------

76. Minimum Window Substring

Idea:
Smallest substring containing every character of target.

Store:
Need Frequency
Window Frequency

Valid:
formed == required

Return:
Substring

---------------------------------------------------------

424. Longest Repeating Character Replacement

Idea:
Replace at most k characters to make all characters same.

Store:
Character Frequency

Valid:
Window Size - Max Frequency <= k

Return:
Maximum Length

---------------------------------------------------------

1004. Max Consecutive Ones III

Idea:
Flip at most k zeros.

Store:
Zero Count

Valid:
Zero Count <= k

Return:
Maximum Length

---------------------------------------------------------

1493. Longest Subarray of 1's After Deleting One Element

Idea:
Delete exactly one element.

Store:
Zero Count

Valid:
Zero Count <= 1

Return:
Maximum Length

---------------------------------------------------------

930. Binary Subarrays With Sum

Idea:
Count subarrays having given binary sum.

Pattern:
Sliding Window + Prefix Sum Thinking

---------------------------------------------------------

992. Subarrays with K Different Integers

Idea:
Count subarrays with exactly K distinct integers.

Store:
Frequency Map

Valid:
Distinct <= K

Interview Trick:
Exactly(K) = AtMost(K) - AtMost(K-1)

---------------------------------------------------------

# Master Template

Expand Right

↓

Update Data Structure

↓

Window Valid?

↓

YES

↓

Update Answer

↓

Shrink Left

↓

Still Valid?

↓

YES → Continue Shrinking

↓

NO

↓

Expand Again